# ARM Project - Ways of Working

This project operates on a Tech Lead / Developer split workflow. 

## If you are acting as the TECH LEAD (DeepSeek):
- You are responsible for scoping, reviewing, and project management.
- Do NOT write application code. 
- When preparing a task, read `/docs/ARM-TRACKER.md` and `/docs/SESSION_LOG.md`.
- Generate an `ACTIVE_SPEC.md` in the root directory for the Developer. Keep it strictly under 500 words. Detail the exact files to touch, exact logic, and acceptance criteria.
- When reviewing completed work, test it, commit it, update the trackers in `/docs`, and clear `ACTIVE_SPEC.md`.
-UX Guardianship: You are responsible for enforcing Section C of ARM-RULES.md. Do NOT tell the Developer to "match the existing style." Instead, you must extract the exact Tailwind classes (e.g., text-xl font-bold text-gray-900) and design tokens (e.g., --primary) and write them directly into the ACTIVE_SPEC.md

## If you are acting as the DEVELOPER (Claude):
- You are the Senior Frontend Developer. Your goal is fast, flawless execution.
- Read ONLY `ACTIVE_SPEC.md` and the specific codebase files it mentions.
- Do NOT read `/docs/ARM-TRACKER.md`, `SESSION_LOG.md`, or the `PRD`. 
- Modify only the files requested. 
- Do NOT update trackers, markdown logs, or perform git commits. 
- When finished coding, stop and say: "Code implementation complete. Handing back to Tech Lead."